# AI Coding Meta-Rules

## Communication with AI
- Be specific in your requests — include file names, function names, expected behavior
- Provide context: "I'm building a Next.js e-commerce app with Prisma and Stripe"
- Break complex tasks into smaller, focused requests
- Ask AI to explain its decisions — catch issues before they become bugs

## Code Review AI Output
- Always review generated code before accepting
- Verify imports are correct and packages are installed
- Check for hardcoded values that should be environment variables
- Ensure error handling is present (AI often generates happy-path only)
- Verify TypeScript types are correct (not `any`)

## AI-Friendly Code
- Write descriptive function and variable names (helps AI understand context)
- Add JSDoc/docstrings for complex functions
- Keep files focused — one concern per file
- Use consistent patterns across your codebase

## What AI Does Well
- Boilerplate generation and scaffolding
- Writing tests for existing code
- Refactoring with clear instructions
- Converting between formats/languages
- Adding error handling and edge cases

## What AI Struggles With
- Complex state management across many files
- Performance optimization without profiling data
- Security-critical code (always review manually)
- Maintaining consistency across large codebases
- Understanding implicit business rules
